{{Infobox journal | title = Journal for the Study of the Old Testament | cover = JSOT.gif | editor = John Jarick, Yvonne Sherwood | abbreviation = J. Study Old Testam. | frequency = 5/year | discipline = [[Biblical studies]] | publisher = [[Sage Publications]] | country = | history = 1976-present | website = http://www.sagepub.com/journals/Journal201752/title | link1 = http://jot.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://jot.sagepub.com/content/by/year | ISSN = 0309-0892 | OCLC = 216746574 | LCCN = 80641375 }} The '''''Journal for the Study of the Old Testament''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering the field of [[biblical studies]]. The [[editors-in-chief]] are David Shepherd ([[Trinity College Dublin]]) and Lena-Sofia Tiemeyer ([[University of Aberdeen]]). It was established in 1976 and is published by [[Sage Publications]].
The journal is associated with the [[Sheffield school]] approach, which engages in literary readings of the [[Canonical criticism|final form]] of the biblical text.<ref>[[Tremper Longman]], ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=oP8uLGkq8EsC&pg=PA112 Literary Approaches to Biblical Interpretation]'', p. 112.</ref><ref>Michael E. Travers, "[https://books.google.com/books?id=I8UWJohMGUIC&pg=PA231 Formalism]," in ''Dictionary for Theological Interpretation of the Bible'', p. 231.</ref>
